gomodel:SYNGO_4814  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: InSyn1 localization to the iPSD is DGC dependent. InSyn1-HA localization after αDG (alpha-dystroglycan) or gephyrin CRISPR depletion. Neurons were depleted of αDG or gephyrin, followed by AAV:InSyn1-HA transduction 3 days before fixation.\n\nFigure 2: The N-terminus of InSyn1 is essential for its localization and interaction with DGC (dystroglycan complex) components.\n\nFigure 5: Altered distribution of GABAAR clustering in InSyn1 KO neurons. Authors conclude that \"InSyn1 has a subunit-specific effect on GABAARs distribution in hippocampal neurons\". Experimental description: M&M: \"InSyn1 KO mice were generated by CRISPR/Cas9 gene-editing method at the Duke Transgenic Core Facility\"\n\n\"Primary neuronal cultures from mouse hippocampus were prepared as described previously\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4814" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

